com.esri.mo2.client.aims
Class Folder

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.esri.mo2.client.aims.Folder
public class Folder
extends Object

The folder object represents a folder in the ArcIMS Administrator. The list of folders in Administrator are categorized into 3 types:

     - EditNote
     - MapNote
     - Other

The folder will be of one of these types.

This class is used by the BaseFolderProxy class to send FolderItems(cookie data) to folders on the the Application Server.

The following classes are used by Folder:

     - com.esri.mo2.client.io.BaseEsrimap
     - FolderItems

Example:


      Folder _folder = new Folder(_emap, cat[0].getName());
       _folder.setDescription(cat[0].getSummary());
       String d = cat[0].getExpiration();
       if ( d != null ) {
         _folder.setExpirationDate(d);
         _folder.setExpires(true)
       }
